{"questionId":"9076295","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The graph shows the observed spectrum from star X.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/f26380af7a14d59ce9d019200df72553a464ab82.png\" alt=\"M18/4/PHYSI/SP3/ENG/TZ1/11_01\"></p>\n<p>The second graph shows the hydrogen emission spectrum in the visible range.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/7c1ca6f68520e84085d01304ae34bc244e39c5a8.png\" alt=\"M18/4/PHYSI/SP3/ENG/TZ1/11_02\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The following diagram shows the main sequence.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/d8831acbe364cc6500017475a693b07ecc3bc8df.png\" alt=\"M18/4/PHYSI/SP3/ENG/TZ1/11.b\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Estimate the mass of star X (<em>M</em><sub>X</sub>) in terms of the mass of the Sun (<em>M</em><sub>s</sub>).</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em>M</em><sub>X</sub> = <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{(35)^{\\frac{1}{{3.5}}}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n    <mn>35</mn>\n    <msup>\n      <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <mfrac>\n          <mn>1</mn>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>3.5</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </mfrac>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span><em>M</em><sub>s</sub></p>\n<p><em>M</em><sub>X</sub> = 2.8<em>M</em><sub>s</sub></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Allow ECF from (b)(i).</em></p>\n<p><em>Do not accept M<sub>X</sub> = (35)</em><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"^{\\frac{1}{{3.5}}}\">\n  <msup>\n    <mi></mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>3.5</mn>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n  </msup>\n</math></span><em> for first marking point.</em></p>\n<p><em>Accept values in the range:&nbsp;2.6 to 2.9M<sub>s</sub>.</em></p>\n<p><strong><em>[2 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"quest